# rclone Configuration for Google Drive Backup
#
# This file is a placeholder. Do NOT copy this file directly.
# Instead, run 'rclone config' to set up your Google Drive connection.
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Install rclone: winget install rclone
# 2. Run: rclone config
# 3. Choose: n (New remote)
# 4. Name: gdrive
# 5. Storage: Google Drive (typically option 18 or search for "drive")
# 6. Leave client_id and client_secret blank (press Enter)
# 7. Scope: 1 (Full access)
# 8. Leave service_account_file blank
# 9. Edit advanced config: n
# 10. Use auto config: y
# 11. Complete OAuth in browser
# 12. Configure as Shared Drive: y
# 13. Select the "ra-all-purpose-backup" shared drive
# 14. Confirm settings: y
#
# Test your configuration:
#   rclone ls gdrive:ra-infrastructure-backup/
#
# The backup script expects:
# - Remote name: gdrive
# - Folder path: ra-infrastructure-backup/
#
# Your actual config will be stored at:
# Windows: %APPDATA%\rclone\rclone.conf
